Assignment 1 - 
Create a table named table_truncate 
Use variables Gender (varchar(255)) and Age (integer) 
Add the following values into table_truncate ('Male', 45) ('Female', 27) ('Male', 33) ('Female', 38) 
Select all the columns of the table and show the result Delete all the values of the table

Solution:

CREATE TABLE table_truncate (
    Gender VARCHAR(255),
    Age INTEGER
);

INSERT INTO table_truncate (Gender, Age) VALUES
('Male', 45),
('Female', 27),
('Male', 33),
('Female', 38);

SELECT * FROM table_truncate;

TRUNCATE TABLE table_truncate;


Assignment 2 - 
Create a table named table_check
Use variables Gender (varchar(255)) and Age (integer)
Use CHECK function so that the column salary does not accept values less than 10000 USD.

Solution:

CREATE TABLE table_check (
    Gender VARCHAR(255),
    Age INTEGER,
    Salary INTEGER 
    CHECK (Salary >= 10000)
);


Assignment 3 - 
Open your MySQL workbench
Create a table using the following information:
Table name: table_modify_col
Columns & datatypes: StudentNames (varchar(255)), Age (float)
Insert the following values:
("Alex", 18.43)
("Akash", 27.56)
("Ramisha", 21.45)
Write necessary code to change the datatype of Age into integer

Solution: 

CREATE TABLE table_modify_col (
    StudentNames VARCHAR(255),
    Age FLOAT
);

INSERT INTO table_modify_col (StudentNames, Age)
VALUES
('Alex', 18.43),
('Akash', 27.56),
('Ramisha', 21.45);
ALTER TABLE table_modify_col
MODIFY Age INT;

